					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the <hi rend="italic">dhvaja staṁbha</hi> in front of the Sōmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>Records the renovation of the temples in Koḷḷipāka and the setting up of the <hi rend="italic">makara tōraṇa</hi> by Gosaraṇārya who claims to have obtained the fiefdom of Koḷḷipāke and the office of the <hi rend="italic">daṇḍādhīśvara</hi> from Simhachakrēśvara. <hi rend="italic">Sēnabōva</hi> Chāvuṇḍamayya wrote the record.</p>						

						<p>The record is not dated and is in characters of about the 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
